  "text": "To explore whether the localizations and/or functions of POL family members are controlled by acylation, we examined the roles of myristoylation and palmitoylation in POL and PLL1 localization in planta. Constructs were generated encoding POL-green fluorescent protein (GFP) and PLL1-GFP fusion proteins under control of the 35S promoter ( Figure 1B ). Additional constructs were also generated that were identical except for substitutions in the first 18 amino acids designed to eliminate myristoylation (myr m ) and/or palmitoylation (pal m ) [CITATION_1] . Specifically, POLmyr m -GFP and PLL1myr m -GFP have the Gly residues presumed to be required for myristoyl attachment changed to Ala residues and the third amino acids altered to residues that would block myristoylation [CITATION_2] . POLpal m -GFP and PLL1pal m -GFP have the Cys residues that are the putative palmitoylation sites changed to Gly residues. POLmyr m pal m -GFP and PLL1myr m pal m -GFP have both sets of key residues disrupted.",
